solution: ```class Solution {
    public long waysToBuyPensPencils(int total, int cost1, int cost2) {
        long ways = 0;
        if (cost1 == 0 && cost2 == 0) return 1;
        if (cost1 == 0) {
            ways = (long) total / cost2 + 1;
            return ways;
        }
        if (cost2 == 0) {
            ways = (long) total / cost1 + 1;
            return ways;
        }
        int maxPens = total / cost1;
        for (int pens = 0; pens <= maxPens; pens++) {
            int remaining = total - pens * cost1;
            if (remaining < 0) break;
            ways += remaining / cost2 + 1;
        }
        return ways;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(total / cost1)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Iterate over every possible count of pens (0 to total/cost1). For each count, compute how many pencils can be bought with the remaining money (remaining/cost2 + 1). Sum these counts. Handles edge cases where either cost is zero.

